\begin_layout Standard
One of the original design goals of the 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

-reactors was that the reactors should have a high sensitivity to able to
 measure on very small amounts of catalyst.
 During the measurements on the oscillations, it turned out that we were
 in fact able to reach full conversion on samples with even very small amounts
 of catalyst.
 At some point we thought that it would be interesting to test how small
 amount of catalyst we can actually get to full conversion.
 To test the sensitivity we have performed a series of tests using CO oxidation
 on Pt thin films as test reaction.
